  I was not fighting a mob that was a caster but the pet was a caster.  My husband also had this happen to him while boxing my chanter. It was a warrior that time that just randomly broke dc. I left a bugreport on it cuz it just doesnt seem right that the skill which costs us 9 points to buy will just behave like any other charm spell. <br>
  Needless to say this is very discouraging and I cannot try soloing again until this situation is adressed. Has anyone else seen anything like this? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=yilini87>yilini87</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#330000>(9/4/03 11:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=240.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dire Charm Breaking??</span><hr size=1> Yes DC can be dispelled.<br>
